edResources()` methods\n  - Client and server stream implementations for bidirectional streaming\n\n- **Stream Processing**: \n  - `pkg/server/sotw/v3/server.go`: Implements `StreamHandler()` for state-of-the-world streaming logic\n  - `pkg/server/delta/v3/server.go`: Implements `DeltaStreamHandler()` for delta (incremental) updates\n\n### 3. Envoy Data Plane Client (envoy C++)\n\nThe `envoyproxy/envoy` repository implements the xDS client subscription logic:\n\n- **Subscription Adapter**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h` and `.cc`\n  - `GrpcSubscriptionImpl`: Adapts typed Subscription to untyped GrpcMux\n  - Implements per-xDS API stats/logging and handles initialization timeouts\n  - Methods: `start()`, `updateResourceInterest()`, `onConfigUpdate()`\n  - Line 24-28: Constructor takes GrpcMux, callbacks, resource decoder, stats, and type_url\n  - Line 40: Calls `grpc_mux_->addWatch()` to register watch with the multiplexer\n\n- **gRPC Multiplexer**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h` and `.cc`\n  - `GrpcMuxImpl`: Manages multiple xDS API streams through a single gRPC connection\n  - Multiplexes different resource types (LDS, CDS, RDS, EDS) onto the AggregatedDiscoveryService stream\n  - Handles request batching and response routing\n\n- **Updated Multiplexer**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h` and `.cc`\n  - `NewGrpcMuxImpl`: Extended multiplexer supporting both SOTW and Delta xDS\n  - Better resource state management and failure handling\n\n- **Stream Communication**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h`\n  - `GrpcStream<RequestProto, ResponseProto>`: Template-based bidirectional gRPC stream\n  - Manages connection establishment, reconnection logic with exponential backoff\n  - Rate limiting of requests (configurable token bucket)\n  - Lines 51-70: `establishNewStream()` creates new bidirectional stream to management server\n  - Line 74: `sendMessag