  "text": "## xDS Configuration Delivery Chain\n\nThe xDS configuration delivery flow from control plane to Envoy data plane comprises three major components:\n\n### 1. Protocol Definition (data-plane-api)\n\nThe `envoyproxy/data-plane-api` repository defines the gRPC service contracts and message types for xDS:\n\n- **Service Definition**: `envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto` defines the `AggregatedDiscoveryService` with two primary RPC methods:\n  - `StreamAggregatedResources(stream DiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DiscoveryResponse)` - State-of-the-world (SOTW) xDS\n  - `DeltaAggregatedResources(stream DeltaDiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DeltaDiscoveryResponse)` - Delta xDS\n\n- **Message Types**: `envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto` defines the core protocol buffers:\n  - `DiscoveryRequest`: Contains version_info, node, resource_names, type_url, and response_nonce\n  - `DiscoveryResponse`: Contains version_info, resources (as google.protobuf.Any), type_url, and nonce\n  - `DeltaDiscoveryRequest` and `DeltaDiscoveryResponse`: Variants for incremental updates\n\n- **Backward Compatibility**: `envoy/api/v2/discovery.proto` and `envoy/service/discovery/v2/ads.proto` provide v2 API definitions for legacy support\n\n### 2. Control Plane Server (go-control-plane)\n\nThe `envoyproxy/go-control-plane` repository implements the server-side xDS management server:\n\n- **Main Handler**: `pkg/server/v3/server.go` implements `StreamAggregatedResources()` which routes to the appropriate stream handler\n  - Line 189: `func (s *server) StreamAggregatedResources(stream discovery.AggregatedDiscoveryService_StreamAggregatedResourcesServer) error`\n  - Line 190: Delegates to `s.StreamHandler(stream, resource.AnyType)` for multiplexed resource handling\n\n- **Generated gRPC Code**: `envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads_grpc.pb.go` contains protoc-generated Go gRPC bindings:\n  - `AggregatedDiscoveryServiceServer` interface with `StreamAggregatedResources()` and `DeltaAggregatedResources()` methods\n  - Client and server stream implementations for bidirectional streaming\n\n- **Stream Processing**: \n  - `pkg/server/sotw/v3/server.go`: Implements `StreamHandler()` for state-of-the-world streaming logic\n  - `pkg/server/delta/v3/server.go`: Implements `DeltaStreamHandler()` for delta (incremental) updates\n\n### 3. Envoy Data Plane Client (envoy C++)\n\nThe `envoyproxy/envoy` repository implements the xDS client subscription logic:\n\n- **Subscription Adapter**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h` and `.cc`\n  - `GrpcSubscriptionImpl`: Adapts typed Subscription to untyped GrpcMux\n  - Implements per-xDS API stats/logging and handles initialization timeouts\n  - Methods: `start()`, `updateResourceInterest()`, `onConfigUpdate()`\n  - Line 24-28: Constructor takes GrpcMux, callbacks, resource decoder, stats, and type_url\n  - Line 40: Calls `grpc_mux_->addWatch()` to register watch with the multiplexer\n\n- **gRPC Multiplexer**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h` and `.cc`\n  - `GrpcMuxImpl`: Manages multiple xDS API streams through a single gRPC connection\n  - Multiplexes different resource types (LDS, CDS, RDS, EDS) onto the AggregatedDiscoveryService stream\n  - Handles request batching and response routing\n\n- **Updated Multiplexer**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h` and `.cc`\n  - `NewGrpcMuxImpl`: Extended multiplexer supporting both SOTW and Delta xDS\n  - Better resource state management and failure handling\n\n- **Stream Communication**: `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h`\n  - `GrpcStream<RequestProto, ResponseProto>`: Template-based bidirectional gRPC stream\n  - Manages connection establishment, reconnection logic with exponential backoff\n  - Rate limiting of requests (configurable token bucket)\n  - Lines 51-70: `establishNewStream()` creates new bidirectional stream to management server\n  - Line 74: `sendMessage()` sends DiscoveryRequest to server\n  - Handles both SOTW (`DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse`) and Delta (`DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse`) variants\n\n## Configuration Flow Sequence\n\n1. **Envoy Startup**: Envoy creates a GrpcSubscriptionImpl for each xDS resource type (listeners, clusters, routes, etc.)\n2. **Subscription Registration**: GrpcSubscriptionImpl calls `GrpcMux::addWatch()` to register interest in resources\n3. **Stream Establishment**: GrpcMux creates a GrpcStream that establishes a bidirectional gRPC connection to the management server using the AggregatedDiscoveryService/StreamAggregatedResources RPC\n4. **Request Sending**: Envoy sends DiscoveryRequest messages containing:\n   - version_info: Current known version (empty on first request)\n   - type_url: The resource type being requested (e.g., type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.v3.Listener)\n   - resource_names: Specific resource names to subscribe to\n   - response_nonce: For ACK/NACK responses\n5. **Server Processing**: The control plane server (go-control-plane) receives the request in StreamAggregatedResources() handler\n6. **Response Sending**: Server sends DiscoveryResponse with:\n   - version_info: New configuration version\n   - resources: Serialized protobuf resources\n   - type_url: Matching the request\n   - nonce: For pairing with subsequent ACK/NACK\n7. **Configuration Update**: Envoy processes DiscoveryResponse, validates config, and either ACKs (sends new request with same version_info and nonce) or NACKs (sends error_detail)\n8. **Stream Lifecycle**: The gRPC stream remains open, allowing push-based updates. If connection fails, GrpcStream automatically reconnects using backoff strategy\n\n## Delta xDS Variant\n\nFor resource-efficient updates, the Delta xDS variant uses:\n- `DeltaDiscoveryRequest`: Includes only changed resources and removals\n- `DeltaDiscoveryResponse`: Includes only delta resources and nonce (required for acknowledgment)\n- Implemented in parallel infrastructure: `DeltaAggregatedResources` RPC in `ads.proto`\n- Delta state management in `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/delta_subscription_state.h`"
